<topic id="e08466be-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2" revisionNumber="1">
	<developerSDKTechnologyOverviewOrientationDocument
	  xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
	  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

		<introduction>
			<para>
				<token>DA</token> maintains preference settings that allow a user to control interaction with all characters.
				The <token>AdvancedCharacterOptions</token> window displays these options and their current
				settings, and can be shown by any hosting application using the <token>DA</token> programming interface.
				<token>DA</token> remembers the last page viewed and displays that page when the property sheet appears.
			</para>
			<autoOutline/>
		</introduction>

		<section address="Output">
			<title>
				The <token>OutputPage</token>
			</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					This page includes properties that control character output. For example, the user can decide whether
					to display output in the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Balloon">
						<token>WordBalloon</token>
					</link>,
					decide how the <link xlink:href="e08466bc-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#Balloon">
						<token>WordBalloon</token>
					</link>
					output should appear, play spoken output as audio, play
					character sound effects, and adjust the speaking speed.
				</para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image xlink:href="Options_Output" />
				</mediaLink>
			</content>
		</section>

		<section address="SpeechInput">
			<title>
				The <token>InputPage</token>
			</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					A user can adjust speech input options on this property page. The user can disable speech input, set
					the <token>ListeningKey</token>, choose whether to display the <token>ListeningTip</token>, and choose to play
					a tone to indicate when speech input is available.
				</para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image xlink:href="Options_SpeechInput" />
				</mediaLink>
			</content>
		</section>

		<section address="Gallery">
			<title>
				The <token>GalleryPage</token>
			</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					As an alternative to loading a specific character, applications can load a character that is a shared
					resource for the user, known as the <newTerm>default character</newTerm>. The <newTerm>default character</newTerm> is available
					to any application, but only the user can select it. The <token>GalleryPage</token> allows the
					user to select the <newTerm>default character</newTerm>.
				</para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image xlink:href="Options_Gallery" />
				</mediaLink>
				<alert class="note">
					<para>
						The <token>GalleryPage</token> used to be in the
						<token>DefaultCharacterProperties</token> window, which no longer exists as of <token>DA</token>
						version 1.1.
					</para>
				</alert>
			</content>
		</section>

		<section address="Copyright">
			<title>The Copyright Page</title>
			<content>
				<para>
					This page displays the copyright and version information for <token>DA</token> and <token>MA</token>.
				</para>
				<mediaLink>
					<image xlink:href="Options_Copyright" />
				</mediaLink>
			</content>
		</section>

